<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<chapter xml:id="ch1-intro-to-standards" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Introduction to Mathematical Standards</title>

  <introduction>
    <p> 
      Most professional organizations have some policies that govern the profession.  These <em>Standards</em> 
      are usually based on research in the respective fields of study and are accompanied by practical 
      guidelines for how the standards should be implemented.  Mathematics Education is no different.  In this 
      chapter, we will examine these standards and how they came to be along with some basic theories on the 
      teaching and learning of mathematics.
    </p>

    
  </introduction>

